doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    title Vidly Movie Rental API
    meta(charset="UTF-8")
    meta(name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0")
    link(rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css")
    style.
      body {
        font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
        background-color: #f8f9fa;
        color: #343a40;
      }

      header {
        background-color: #007bff;
        color: white;
        padding: 2rem 0;
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        border-radius: 10px;
        animation: fadeIn 1s ease-out;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        font-weight: bold;
      }

      section {
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        background-color: white;
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        opacity: 0;
        animation: fadeIn 1s ease-out forwards;
      }

      h2 {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        font-size: 1.75rem;
        color: #0056b3;
      }

      h3 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
      }

      ol li, ul li {
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }

      a {
        color: #007bff;
        text-decoration: none;
        position: relative;
        transition: color 0.3s ease-in-out;
      }

      a:hover {
        color: #0056b3;
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      a::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        width: 100%;
        height: 2px;
        bottom: 0;
        left: 0;
        background-color: #0056b3;
        visibility: hidden;
        transform: scaleX(0);
        transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out;
      }

      a:hover::before {
        visibility: visible;
        transform: scaleX(1);
      }

      footer {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        padding-top: 1rem;
        border-top: 1px solid #dee2e6;
      }

      pre {
        background-color: #f1f3f5;
        padding: 0.75rem;
        border-radius: 5px;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }

      /* Fade-in animation */
      @keyframes fadeIn {
        0% {
          opacity: 0;
          transform: translateY(20px);
        }
        100% {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: translateY(0);
        }
      }

  body
    .container
      header
        h1 Vidly Movie Rental API
        p Built using Express, MongoDB, and Pug by Ahmad

      section
        h2 Setup

        p To run this project, ensure you have Node.js v20 or above installed. You can download it at 
          a(href="https://nodejs.org", target="_blank") nodejs.org.

        h3 Steps to Get Started

        ol
          li 
            h4 Clone the repository
            pre 
              code 
                | git clone https://github.com/dd3vahmad/vidly.git

          li 
            h4 Install dependencies
            pre 
              code 
                | npm install

          li 
            h4 Set up environment variables
            p The app uses MongoDB as the database. You need to create a `.env` file in the root of your project with the following variables:
            pre
              code 
                | MONGO_URI=your-mongodb-uri
                | PORT=3000

          li 
            h4 Run the app
            pre 
              code 
                | npm run dev

        h3 Live Preview
        p
          a(href="https://github.com/dd3vahmad/vidly", target="_blank") View the source code on GitHub

      section
        h2 Features of the API

        ul
          li Comprehensive movie rental management (CRUD operations for movies, rentals, and customers)
          li Secure user authentication using JWT
          li Robust validation with Joi for input data
          li MongoDB as a NoSQL database
          li Pagination and sorting for large datasets
          li API rate limiting and error handling

      section
        h2 Tools & Technologies Used

        ul
          li Express.js - Fast, unopinionated web framework for Node.js
          li MongoDB - NoSQL database for storing movie and rental data
          li Pug - Template engine for rendering the frontend
          li JWT - Authentication using JSON Web Tokens
          li Joi - Input validation
          li Morgan - HTTP request logging

      footer
        p I'm happy if you find this project interesting. Feel free to 
          a(href="https://github.com/dd3vahmad/vidly/issues", target="_blank") create an issue
          |  if you'd like to suggest anything.

        p Big thanks to 
          a(href="https://x.com/moshhamedani", target="_blank") Mosh Hamedani 
          | for his amazing courses that helped me build this API!
